
                                            Jacques Pauw’s book ‘The President’s Keepers’ contains allegations against President Jacob Zuma relating to corruption and irregularities with his tax affairs.
                                         JOHANNESBURG - The Right2Know Campaign says the State Security Agency (SSA)’s threats against Jacques Pauw and his publisher is a crude act of censorship. Pauw’s book The President’s Keepers contains allegations against President Jacob Zuma relating to corruption and irregularities with his tax affairs. The agency wants parts of the book to be retracted, but his publisher says their lawyers are now dealing with the matter and there’s no intention of withdrawing the book at this stage. The campaign’s Murray Hunter says this is a desperate attempt. “They’re trying to close the book and bury it. This is the sort of secret tactics that we’re seeing from the State Security Agency now.” Read the full document below:    Cease Desist by Primedia Broadcasting on Scribd 